    "### The image can be sliced to trim it, which is useful for focusing on specific areas of the image."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "81accc57",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",

     "data": {

    },
    {
     "data": {

       "<Figure size 300x300 with 1 Axes>"

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Read image\n",
    "image = cv2.imread(path + '/nature.jpg')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Show image and its slicing\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))\n",
    "plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))\n",
    "plt.title(\"Image\")\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Slicing the image to focus on a specific area\n",
    "image_crop = image[50:150, 500:700]\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(3,3))\n",
    "plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(image_crop, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))\n",
    "plt.title(\"Slicing\")\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

    "## Rotate image with NumPy: `np.rot90()`"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "01d9f2b5",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "### We can pass arguments to `np.rot90()`, defaulting to 1 rotation (90 degrees), 2 rotations (180 degrees), or 3 rotations (270 degrees). The `k` parameter specifies the number of times to rotate the image by 90 degrees."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "5b1c4de9",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x600 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Convert image to RGB for display because OpenCV loads images in BGR format\n",
    "image_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n",
    "image_rot_90 = np.rot90(image_rgb, k=1)\n",
    "image_rot_180 = np.rot90(image_rgb, k=2)\n",
    "image_rot_270 = np.rot90(image_rgb, k=3)\n",
    "image_rot_360 = np.rot90(image_rgb, k=4)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(8, 6))\n",
    "axes[0, 0].imshow(image_rot_90)\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_title(\"Rotated 90°\")\n",
    "axes[0, 1].imshow(image_rot_180)\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_title(\"Rotated 180°\")\n",
    "axes[1, 0].imshow(image_rot_270)\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_title(\"Rotated 270°\")\n",
    "axes[1, 1].imshow(image_rot_360)\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_title(\"Rotated 360°\")\n",
    "for ax in axes.flat:\n",
    "    ax.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "## Flipping image"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "efea92b9",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "### Manually"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3566b4ec",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Vertically"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "id": "c75e2b15",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "img = plt.imread(path + '/nature.jpg')\n",
    "img = img.astype(float)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Take shapes (height, width, channel)\n",
    "height, width, channels = img.shape\n",
    "\n",
    "# Transform matrix (flip wrt x axis, or i.e., vertical flip)\n",
    "transform = np.array([[1, 0], [0, -1]])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize output matrix with same shape as input image\n",
    "output = np.zeros((height, width, channels))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Iterate over each pixel in the original image\n",
    "for h in range(height):\n",
    "    for w in range(width):\n",
    "        pixel = img[h, w, :]\n",
    "        new_j, new_i = transform@np.array([w, h]) + [0, height - 1]\n",
    "        output[new_i, new_j] = pixel\n",
    "\n",
    "output = output.astype(np.uint8)\n",
    "plt.imsave(path + '/vertically_flipped.jpg', output)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))\n",
    "plt.imshow(output)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Flipped vertically\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "68e50482",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Horizontally"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "id": "30b36a4e",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "img = plt.imread(path + '/nature.jpg')\n",
    "img = img.astype(float)\n",
    "\n",
    "height, width, channels = img.shape\n",
    "transform = np.array([[-1, 0], [0, 1]])\n",
    "output = np.zeros((height, width, channels))\n",
    "for h in range(height):\n",
    "    for w in range(width):\n",
    "        pixel = img[h, w, :]\n",
    "        new_j, new_i = transform@np.array([w, h]) + [width - 1, 0]\n",
    "        output[new_i, new_j] = pixel\n",
    "\n",
    "output = output.astype(np.uint8)\n",
    "plt.imsave(path + '/horizontally_flipped.jpg', output)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))\n",
    "plt.imshow(output)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Flipped horizontally\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8b4cfa72",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",

   "source": [
    "### Using built-in functions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e405eed1",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "#### Using `cv2.flip()`\n",
    "`flipCode` can be:\n",
    "- `0`: flip vertically\n",
    "- `1`: flip horizontally\n",
    "- `-1`: flip both vertically and horizontally"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "id": "20b99b67",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x400 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "img = plt.imread(path + '/nature.jpg')\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(12, 4), constrained_layout=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "titles = [\n",
    "    \"Original\",\n",
    "    \"Flipped vertically\",\n",
    "    \"Flipped horizontally\",\n",
    "    \"Flipped vertically & horizontally\"\n",
    "]\n",
    "images = [\n",
    "    img,\n",
    "    cv2.flip(img, 0),\n",
    "    cv2.flip(img, 1),\n",
    "    cv2.flip(img, -1)\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(4):\n",
    "    ax[i].imshow(images[i])\n",
    "    ax[i].set_title(titles[i], fontsize=12)\n",
    "    ax[i].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2577e735",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "## Increase/Decrease brightness\n",
    "Because OpenCV images contain uint8 pixel values (range [0,255]), so we must convert to float to avoid overflow when adding or subtracting brightness values. After processing, we convert back to uint8."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6155abff",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "We can implement in 3 ways: `loop`, `np.clip()`, and `np.where()`.\n",
    "- Example of using `loop`:\n",
    "```python\n",
    "for i in range(image.shape[0]):\n",
    "    for j in range(image.shape[1]):\n",
    "        for k in range(image.shape[2]):\n",
    "            image[i, j, k] = np.clip(image[i, j, k] + brightness, 0, 255)\n",
    "```\n",
    "- Example of using `np.clip()` in the cell below\n",
    "- Example of using `np.where()`:\n",
    "```python\n",
    "image = np.where(image + brightness > 255, 255, image + brightness)\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cfbf2cfc",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "### Increase brightness"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "id": "9e5713a4",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 400x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "image_bright_dec80 = image_rgb.copy()\n",
    "image_bright_dec80 = image_bright_dec80.astype(float)\n",
    "\n",
    "image_bright_dec80 -= 80\n",
    "image_bright_dec80 = np.clip(image_bright_dec80, 0, 255)\n",
    "image_bright_dec80 = image_bright_dec80.astype(np.uint8)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.imsave(path + '/decrease80_clip.jpg', image_bright_dec80)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))\n",
    "plt.imshow(image_bright_dec80)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Decreased 80 brightness\")\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b8694b09",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "### Decrease brightness"
   ]
  },

   },
   "source": [
    "## Background subtraction (or foreground extraction)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "681540b3",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "### Manually"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "id": "3689828b",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 700x300 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "img = plt.imread(path + '/maxresdefault.jpg')\n",
    "rgb8 = (img * 255.0).round().astype(np.uint8) if np.issubdtype(img.dtype, np.floating) else img\n",
    "\n",
    "target = np.array([19, 252, 23], dtype=np.int16)\n",
    "tol = 100\n",
    "diff = np.abs(rgb8.astype(np.int16) - target)\n",
    "is_green = (diff <= tol).all(axis=2)\n",
    "extracted = np.where(is_green[..., None], 0, rgb8).astype(np.uint8)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(7, 3), constrained_layout=True)\n",
    "ax[0].imshow(rgb8);      ax[0].set_title('Before');    ax[0].axis('off')\n",
    "ax[1].imshow(extracted); ax[1].set_title('Extracted'); ax[1].axis('off')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "24909e9c",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "source": [
    "### Using np.subtract()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "id": "5c902d44",
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import cv2\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Magic command to display inline\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load images\n",
    "image_city = plt.imread('images/colorfull-2.jpg')\n",
    "dragon_with_background = plt.imread('images/maxresdefault.jpg')\n",
    "background = plt.imread('images/background.jpg')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ensure all images are uint8 and same shape\n",
    "def to_uint8(img):\n",
    "    if np.issubdtype(img.dtype, np.floating):\n",
    "        img = (img * 255.0).round().astype(np.uint8)\n",
    "    return img\n",
    "\n",
    "image_city = to_uint8(image_city)\n",
    "dragon_with_background = to_uint8(dragon_with_background)\n",
    "background = to_uint8(background)\n",
    "\n",
    "dragon_with_background = cv2.resize(dragon_with_background, (image_city.shape[1], image_city.shape[0]))\n",
    "background = cv2.resize(background, (image_city.shape[1], image_city.shape[0]))"
   ]

     "hide-output",
     "scroll-output"

   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Compute absolute difference between dragon_with_background and background\n",
    "diff = cv2.absdiff(dragon_with_background, background)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create mask: pixels with large difference are foreground (dragon), small difference are background\n",
    "threshold = 100\n",
    "mask = np.any(diff > threshold, axis=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create output: keep dragon where mask is True, else set to transparent (or black)\n",
    "dragon_fg = np.zeros_like(dragon_with_background)\n",
    "dragon_fg = np.where(mask[..., None], dragon_with_background, 0)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.imshow(dragon_fg)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Dragon without background\")\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "id": "b5521834",

   "source": [
    "# Overlay dragon foreground onto city image using mask\n",
    "output = np.where(mask[..., None], dragon_fg, image_city)\n",
    "plt.imshow(output)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Dragon inside the city\")\n",
    "plt.axis('off')\n",
    "plt.show()"
